# CaptionDB Fireworks AI Engineering Contract

## Purpose

This contract defines how Fireworks AI must be integrated into CaptionDB.

Fireworks is the AI inference provider used for the AMD Developer Hackathon.

The implementation must remain provider-independent so that Fireworks can be replaced in the future with minimal code changes.

---

# Engineering Philosophy

Fireworks is an implementation detail.

The application architecture must never depend directly on Fireworks SDK methods.

The rest of the application should depend only on interfaces.

---

# Single Integration Point

Only one service may communicate with Fireworks.

FireworksClient

Every AI request must go through this client.

Never call Fireworks directly from:

Routes

Services

Workers

Components

Pipeline

Prompt Manager

Judge

Memory

OCR

Scene Detection

---

# Responsibilities of FireworksClient

FireworksClient is responsible for:

Authentication

Connection management

Retries

Timeouts

Rate limiting

Structured outputs

Logging

Metrics

Response validation

Error translation

Provider abstraction

Nothing else.

---

# Provider Independence

Business logic must never know:

Fireworks SDK

Fireworks URLs

Fireworks response objects

Fireworks exceptions

Convert Fireworks responses into CaptionDB domain models.

---

# Authentication

API keys must only come from:

Environment variables

Secrets manager (future)

Never hardcode credentials.

Never log API keys.

Never expose keys in exceptions.

---

# Model Configuration

Never hardcode model IDs.

Model configuration belongs in:

models.yaml

or

settings

Support switching models without modifying application logic.

---

# Prompt Handling

Prompt text must never be created inside FireworksClient.

FireworksClient only receives:

System Prompt

User Prompt

Images

Metadata

Generation Settings

Prompt construction belongs elsewhere.

---

# Structured Outputs

Whenever supported, prefer structured outputs over free-form text.

Responses should map into typed models.

Avoid manual string parsing.

---

# Response Validation

Every Fireworks response must be validated.

Check:

Missing fields

Malformed responses

Empty outputs

Unexpected formats

Reject invalid responses gracefully.

---

# Retry Policy

Retry only transient failures.

Examples:

Timeout

429

503

Temporary network failures

Never retry:

Invalid request

Authentication failure

Validation errors

Configuration errors

---

# Exponential Backoff

Retry delays should use exponential backoff.

Backoff values must be configurable.

Avoid retry storms.

---

# Timeout Policy

Every request must define:

Connection timeout

Read timeout

Overall timeout

Never wait indefinitely.

---

# Rate Limiting

Respect Fireworks limits.

Support configurable request throttling.

Queue requests if necessary.

Avoid accidental API flooding.

---

# Parallel Requests

Parallel requests are allowed only when:

Independent

Thread-safe

Within provider limits

Never exceed configured concurrency.

---

# Request Validation

Before sending requests validate:

Prompt

Images

Configuration

Model

Generation settings

Reject invalid requests before contacting Fireworks.

---

# Image Handling

Validate:

Image count

Image format

Image size

Resolution

Encoding

Reject unsupported inputs.

---

# Prompt Versioning

Prompt templates must support versions.

Example:

v1

v2

v3

The selected prompt version should be configurable.

---

# Generation Parameters

Never hardcode:

Temperature

Top P

Max Tokens

Stop Sequences

Frequency Penalty

Presence Penalty

Configuration controls generation.

---

# Metrics

Capture:

Latency

Input tokens

Output tokens

Total tokens

Retry count

Failure reason

Model used

Request duration

Store metrics separately from business logic.

---

# Logging

Log:

Request ID

Model

Latency

Retry count

Success

Failure

Never log:

API keys

Sensitive prompts

Private user data

---

# Error Translation

Translate provider-specific errors into CaptionDB exceptions.

Examples:

FireworksAuthenticationException

↓

ConfigurationException

FireworksTimeoutException

↓

FireworksException

FireworksRateLimitException

↓

RetryableException

The rest of the application should never depend on Fireworks exception classes.

---

# Fallback Strategy

Support future fallback providers.

Example:

Fireworks

↓

Secondary Provider

↓

Local Model

The pipeline should support provider failover through configuration.

---

# Connection Reuse

Reuse HTTP connections whenever possible.

Avoid creating a new client for every request.

Connection pooling should be enabled.

---

# Batch Requests

Where supported and beneficial, batch requests instead of sending many small requests.

Batching must remain configurable.

---

# Streaming

Streaming support should remain optional.

Application logic should function correctly whether streaming is enabled or disabled.

---

# Circuit Breaker

Protect Fireworks from repeated failures.

If repeated failures occur:

Pause requests

Log the issue

Return meaningful errors

Avoid overwhelming the provider.

---

# Caching

Do not cache mutable responses.

Only cache when explicitly enabled.

Examples:

Vision descriptions

Embeddings

Prompt templates

Configuration

Cache policy must be configurable.

---

# Dependency Injection

FireworksClient must be injected.

Never instantiate it inside business logic.

---

# Testing

Mock Fireworks in unit tests.

Never call the real API during automated testing.

Integration tests should remain separate.

---

# Documentation

Document:

Supported models

Configuration

Generation settings

Retry policy

Timeout policy

Failure modes

---

# Self Review Checklist

Before completing implementation verify:

✓ Single integration point

✓ No direct SDK usage outside FireworksClient

✓ Configuration driven

✓ Typed responses

✓ Structured outputs

✓ Retry policy implemented

✓ Timeouts configured

✓ Rate limiting respected

✓ Logging implemented

✓ Metrics collected

✓ API keys protected

✓ Provider independent

✓ Tests added

✓ Documentation updated

If any check fails, revise implementation before completion.

---

End of Fireworks AI Engineering Contract.
